# Multilingual RAG PDF Question Answering with Enhanced Embeddings
This project builds a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system for question answering over PDF documents, with a focus on multilingual support (Persian + English) and embedding comparison for improved retrieval quality.
It explores how different embedding models affect retrieval performance and how LLMs can generate accurate answers based strictly on retrieved context.
________________________________________
🚀 Project Overview
The system follows a full RAG pipeline:
1.	PDF Loading & Splitting
o	Extract text from PDF documents
o	Split into smaller overlapping chunks for better retrieval
2.	Embedding Generation
o	Convert text chunks into dense vector representations
o	Compare multiple embedding models:
	sbunlp/fabert (Persian-focused)
	sentence-transformers/paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2 (multilingual semantic model)
3.	Vector Storage
o	Store embeddings using:
	DocArray In-Memory Search
	FAISS for efficient similarity search
4.	Retrieval
o	Retrieve most relevant document chunks for a given query
5.	LLM Answer Generation
o	Use a Hugging Face LLM pipeline (Gemma 2 9B)
o	Generate answers strictly based on retrieved context
________________________________________
🧠 Key Idea
Instead of relying on raw LLM knowledge, the model:
•	Retrieves relevant passages from the PDF
•	Uses only that context to answer questions
•	Reduces hallucination and improves factual accuracy
________________________________________
